\n|-\n| 17.\n| rowspan=2 | 6 September 2003 || rowspan=2 | Boris Paichadze Stadium, Tbilisi || rowspan=2 | {{fb|ALB}} || '''1'''\u20130 || rowspan=2 | 3\u20130 || rowspan=2 | UEFA Euro 2004 qualifier\n|-\n| 18. || '''3'''\u20130\n|-\n| 19. || 11 September 2003 || Qemal Stafa Stadium, Tirana || {{fb|ALB}} || '''1'''\u20131 || 1\u20132 || UEFA Euro 2004 qualifier\n|-\n| 20. || 27 May 2005 || Sportzentrum, [[Altenkirchen]] || {{fb|NZL}} || '''1'''\u20132 || 1\u20133 || Friendly\n|-\n| 21.\n| rowspan=3 | 18 August 2006 || rowspan=3 | [[Svangaskar\u00f0]], [[Toftir]] || rowspan=3 | {{fb|Faroe Islands}} || '''3'''\u20130 || rowspan=3 | 6\u20130 || rowspan=3 | [[UEFA Euro 2008 qualifying Group B|UEFA Euro 2008 qualifier]]\n|-\n| 22. || '''5'''\u20130\n|-\n| 23. || '''6'''\u20130\n|-\n| 24. || 6 September 2006 || [[Olimpiyskiy National Sports Complex]], [[Kiev]] || {{fb|UKR}} || '''1'''\u20131 || 1\u20132 || UEFA Euro 2008 qualifier\n|-\n| 25. || 16 November 2006 || Mikheil Meskhi Stadium, Tbilisi || {{fb|Jordan}} || '''3'''\u20132 || 3\u20132 || Friendly\n|-\n| 26. || 29 March 2007 || [[Hampden Park]], [[Glasgow]] || {{fb|SCO}} || '''1'''\u20131 || 1\u20132 || UEFA Euro 2008 qualifier\n|}\n\n===Managerial statistics===\n{{updated|13 April 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mackolik.com/Antrenor/1753/Shota-Arveladze|title=Shota Arveladze's Managerial statistics|publisher=mackolik.com|date=19 April 2017|accessdate=19 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Managerial record by team and tenure\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Team\n!rowspan=2|From\n!rowspan=2|To\n!colspan=8|Record\n|-\n!{{Tooltip|G|Games managed}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Games won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Games drawn}}\n!{{Tooltip|L|Games lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n!{{Tooltip|GD|Goal difference}}\n!{{Tooltip|Win %|Winning percentage}}\n|-\n| [[Kayserispor]]\n| 29 June 2010\n| 3 October 2012\n{{WDL|86|33|16|37|for=109|against=117|diff=yes}}\n|-\n| [[Kas\u0131mpa\u015f