132 || [[UEFA Euro 2008 qualifying Group B|UEFA Euro 2008 qualifier]]\n|-\n| 25. || 16 November 2006 || Mikheil Meskhi Stadium, Tbilisi || {{fb|Jordan}} || '''3'''\u20132 || 3\u20132 || Friendly\n|-\n| 26. || 29 March 2007 || [[Hampden Park]], [[Glasgow]] || {{fb|SCO}} || '''1'''\u20131 || 1\u20132 || [[UEFA Euro 2008 qualifying Group B|UEFA Euro 2008 qualifier]]\n|}\n\n===Managerial statistics===\n{{updated|13 April 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mackolik.com/Antrenor/1753/Shota-Arveladze|title=Shota Arveladze's Managerial statistics|publisher=mackolik.com|date=19 April 2017|accessdate=19 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Managerial record by team and tenure\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Team\n!rowspan=2|From\n!rowspan=2|To\n!colspan=8|Record\n|-\n!{{Tooltip|G|Games managed}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Games won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Games drawn}}\n!{{Tooltip|L|Games lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n!{{Tooltip|GD|Goal difference}}\n!{{Tooltip|Win %|Winning percentage}}\n|-\n| [[Kayserispor]]\n| 29 June 2010\n| 3 October 2012\n{{WDL|86|33|16|37|for=109|against=117|diff=yes}}\n|-\n| [[Kas\u0131mpa\u015fa Spor Kul\u00fcb\u00fc|Kas\u0131mpa\u015fa]]\n| 8 October 2012\n| 13 March 2015\n{{WDL|91|33|28|30|for=144|against=126|diff=yes}}\n|-\n| [[Trabzonspor]]\n| 3 July 2015\n| 11 November 2015\n{{WDL|15|6|3|6|for=18|against=18|diff=yes}}\n|-\n| [[Maccabi Tel Aviv F.C.|Maccabi Tel Aviv]]\n| 16 June 2016\n| 4 January 2017\n{{WDL|30|16|7|7|for=52|against=33|diff=yes}}\n|-\n| [[Pakhtakor Tashkent FK|Pakhtakor]]\n| 23 June 2017\n| \n{{WDL|60|40|11|9|for=109|against=46|diff=yes}}\n|-\n! colspan=3|Career totals\n{{WDLtot|282|128|65|89|for=430|against=340|diff=yes}}\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n'''Dinamo Tbilisi'''\n*[[Umaglesi Liga]] (4): [[1991 Umaglesi Liga|1990\u201391]], [[1991\u201392 Umaglesi Liga|1991\u201392]], [[1992\u201393 Umaglesi Liga|1992\u201393]], [[1993\u201394 Umaglesi Liga|1993\u201394]]\n*[[Georgian Cup]] 